0092|SJumping by activating lines starting with `-'
S   | //////////////////////////////////////////////
0093|*By activating a line of the form
0094|S  - Supercalifragilisticexplialidocious thing
S   |  77777777777777777777777777777777777777777777
0095|*i.e. an isolated `-' followed by certain words, the editor tries to
0096|*find those words primarily below the current line and secondarily
0097|*from the beginning of the edit field. If no such words are found,
0098|*nothing happens. Otherwise the cursor is moved to the new line
0099|*containing those words.
0100|*If the new line is similar to the original one, activation of it
0101|*leads back to that original line provided that there are no other
0102|*similar strings in other parts of the edit field.
0104|*This is the fastest way, for example, to accomplish links between an
0105|*index of the form
