0120|#SHOW <file name>,<first line to be shown (optional)>
S   |      <         > <                                 >
0121|*shows portions of edit files and text files in a temporary window
0122|*below the current line (SHOW line). The text may be scrolled in that
0123|*window and selected lines may be copied in the edit field from
0124|*the line below the SHOW line onwards, provided that those lines are
0125|*empty.
0127|*SHOW without any parameters displays the contents of the current out-
0128|*put file set by the OUTPUT operation.
0129|- shadow %: [LINK(q04_07.html)] [/LINK]
0130|SSHOW * displays the current edit field itself.    (See also SHOWKEYS?)
S   |                                                   8888888888%%%%%%%%88
0132|- [New]
0133|*SHOW <file name>,<first line>,n
S   |      <         > <          >
0134|- [/New]
0135|*works as SHOW above but shows at least n lines. Maximum number of
0136|*lines shown depends on the size of the current Survo main window.
0138|*If n is not given, the number of lines of the SHOW window is given
0139|*by the system parameter show_lines in the SURVO.APU file.
0140|*This parameter can be set for the current session by the command
0141|*SYSTEM show_lines=n
0142|*The default setting is show_lines=0 and then SHOW without the n
0143|*parameter shows as many lines as there is place in the current
0144|*main window below the SHOW command line.
0146|*By default, 100000 first lines of a text files can be shown by SHOW.
0147|- [New]
